## Architecture Overview (Essential Knowledge)

### 5 Core Components

1. **Background Service Worker** (`background.js`)
   - Creates/updates context menu dynamically
   - Routes execution messages via `chrome.tabs.sendMessage()`
   - Detects active AI platform from URL
   - Opens new tabs if platform not active
   - Syncs with IndexedDB via listeners

2. **Content Script** (`content.js`)
   - Injected into all webpages
   - Platform detection via CSS selectors
   - Variable replacement: `{{text}}`, `{{url}}`, `{{title}}`
   - Form auto-filling and submit button clicking
   - Message listener for execution commands

3. **Popup UI** (`popup.html`)
   - Quick access dropdown (400x500px)
   - Favorites display with ⭐
   - Real-time search
   - Link to options page

4. **Options Page** (`options.html`)
   - Create/edit/delete prompts
   - Category management
   - Favorites toggling
   - Usage statistics

5. **Data Storage** (Dexie/IndexedDB)
   - `prompts` table (text, category, favorite, usageCount)
   - `categories` table
   - Local-only (no cloud sync)

### Execution Flow
```
User right-click → Context menu → Select prompt → 
Background detects platform → Opens tab if needed → 
Content script injects into AI page → Replace variables → 
Fill textarea → Click submit → Usage count increments
```

